</materialsCitation>
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="8B9936C2CA49FFA6C94B3424FAF2F776" blockId="25.[813,1399,2018,2440]" pageId="25" pageNumber="644">
The Spotted-necked Otter was previously included in the genus 
<taxonomicName id="4C264D41CA49FFA6CE1D3450FB47F7E9" authorityName="Brisson" authorityYear="1762" box="[1144,1217,2136,2165]" class="Mammalia" family="Mustelidae" genus="Lutra" kingdom="Animalia" order="Carnivora" pageId="25" pageNumber="644" phylum="Chordata" rank="genus">Lutra</taxonomicName>
by some authors, but recent molecular studies have shown that its inclusion in 
<taxonomicName id="4C264D41CA49FFA6CEAF34AAFA95F75F" authorityName="Brisson" authorityYear="1762" box="[1226,1299,2210,2243]" class="Mammalia" family="Mustelidae" genus="Lutra" kingdom="Animalia" order="Carnivora" pageId="25" pageNumber="644" phylum="Chordata" rank="genus">Lutra</taxonomicName>
would make this genus paraphyletic. Monotypic.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
